{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"4277d85693ce7ae3559eb0a94f3b50be93446600"},"timestamp":1324312704,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNjAyNTY0","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/233","origin":"github"},"title":"configuration-file interface does not accept arguments with whitespace","message":"Configuration files passed to `perl Configure.pl --file=...` fail to accept arguments with whitespace in the `general` section -- in particular, the following code will fail:\n\n```\n=general\n\nintval=long long\n```\n\nIt's probable that `lib/Parrot/Configure/Options/Conf/File.pm` is to blame, feel free to track this down further.\n\nFor now, I'm using\n\n```\n=variables\n\nLONGLONG=long long\n\n=general\n\nintval=$LONGLONG\n```\n\nas a workaround.","files":null}]}